<subSubSection pageId="229" pageNumber="230" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="229.[151,1436,1581,2037]" pageId="229" pageNumber="230">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1941,1965]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="229" pageNumber="230" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
The yellow crab is a large, heavily calcified intertidal crab. It seems to prefer slightly warmer waters than 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Randall" authorityYear="1840" box="[209,356,1977,2001]" class="Malacostraca" family="Cancridae" genus="Cancer" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="229" pageNumber="230" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="productus">
<emphasis box="[209,228,1977,2001]" italics="true" pageId="229" pageNumber="230">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[245,356,1977,2001]" italics="true" pageId="229" pageNumber="230">productus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Stimpson, 1856)" baseAuthorityName="Stimpson" baseAuthorityYear="1856" box="[417,885,1977,2001]" class="Malacostraca" family="Cancridae" genus="Romaleon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="229" pageNumber="230" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="antennarius">
<emphasis box="[417,675,1977,2001]" italics="true" pageId="229" pageNumber="230">Romaleon antennarius</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Stimpson, W." box="[692,877,1977,2001]" pageId="229" pageNumber="230" pagination="87 - 90" refId="ref237109" refString="Stimpson, W. (1856) On some California Crustacea. Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, 1, 87 - 90." type="journal article" year="1856">Stimpson, 1856</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
; the other similar large crabs that live in rocky habitats. Records north of 
<collectingCountry box="[447,561,2013,2037]" name="Saint Pierre and Miquelon" pageId="229" pageNumber="230">San Pedro</collectingCountry>
usually come from bays and harbors rather than the open coast.
</paragraph>
